snippet.textDisplay: bruh I have Invisalign and they've messed up THREE TIMES. Two of them involved them extremely not fitting to where I couldn't bite down because of them and the other involved them charging twice as much while simultaneously telling my mom we were past due on the payments when we weren't. My bite has changed and I think I have more of an overbite than I had in the first place; half of my tongue can fit put of my mouth without me having to open it. My teeth still aren't very straight and they've made me bleed so much. Also, they told us Ill be wearing retainers "for the rest of my life." Nobody told us about that and I think that would be a pretty big part of the whole thing. It also sucks because when we have issues with them, since theres no appointments, we have to call and deal with rude people, sending pictures which is a pain, etc etc. Invisalign sucks.

snippet.textDisplay:
Saw this video like a week before my wisdom teeth removal, and I thought to myself: "Yeah, don't watch this after you've done it"
Now, 3 days after surgery (all 4 teeth) I can say... as a patient who's struggled with fear of dentists big time in the past... I was ultra chilled, not even flinched once and... well the dentist and the nurses were super nice... also complimented my taste in music, because I wore a bad shirt.
My left cheek is still swolen AF and we went back to the dentist yesterday, because it hurt and was way more swolen than the right one, so he perscirbed me antibiotics and since then everything is working out.


Have to say, I was not scared at all and would say to anybody to get all 4 teeth done (if needed) in one appointment, yeah you won't be able to eat that well (mostly, because you can't open your mouth very well... at least that's it for me), but it's better than doing this 2 times, basically doubling the duration of "pain" (if you are unlucky and have that big of an ache) and time you spent on... basically doing nothing.


Have a great day, and greetings from Germany :)
